What are Design Patterns?
Design Patterns are proven solutions to common software design problems. They help developers write scalable, maintainable, and reusable code by providing structured ways to solve common coding challenges.

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/48c7da8d-ab37-4ef5-b35d-e7cb8a7ced3c)

ðŸ”¹ Singleton Pattern
Ensures that only one instance of a class exists and provides a global point of access.

